                    Building Web API with Flask
                    Course Notes


                    Section 1 - Introduction
1 - Welcome and Setup 
Introduction to the author and the class
Python versions 3.4 & 2.7 have been tested with the examples in the course
Python 3 is recommended by the instructor
The student will also need to have Virtual Environment installed
  - Python 3.4 has virtual env natively
Git will need to be installed to download or clone code used in the course
  - git clone https://github.com/miguelgrinberg/oreilly-flask-apis-video.git
  - The repository is structured so as to show each feature
  
To create virtual environment
  - python 3.4 -m venv venv
  - source venv/bin/activate    -- This activates the virtual environment
  - pip install -r requirements.txt     -- Will install the packages listed in the requirements.txt file

